COPS in Kimberley in the Northern Cape have appealed to SunReaders to help them bust a suspected child snatcher. A woman was spotted attempting to steal a boy (5) in Beaconsfield, a suburb of the Diamond City on 22 May at about 4pm. A concerned resident saw the woman trying to forcibly grab a boy who then cried for help. The concerned resident ran closer and the unknown woman fled the scene. It was later established the woman tried to kidnap the boy but was disturbed by the woman. Police spokesman Captain Sergio Kock said: “A case of attempted kidnapping was opened. Cops request anyone with information to contact Detective-Sergeant David Tau on 083 472 6819. The investigation continues.”